magpie.data.utilities.generators

Class PhaseDiagramCompositionEntryGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.data.utilities.generators.BaseEntryGenerator
      • magpie.data.utilities.generators.PhaseDiagramCompositionEntryGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<BaseEntry>, Options
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    IonicCompoundGenerator

    public class PhaseDiagramCompositionEntryGenerator
extends BaseEntryGenerator
    Generate composition entries at many points in many phase diagrams.

    Has two different ways of selecting compositions within phase diagrams

    1. Even Spacing: Compositions are selected as to be evenly-spaced throughout the phase diagram (e.g. A0.2B0.2C0.6, A0.4B0.2C0.4, etc.). This method is most appropriate for alloy systems.
    2. Simple Fractions: Compositions with the smallest denominator are selected. (e.g ABC, A2C, B2C, etc.). This method is most appropriate for phase diagrams that represent ordered crystalline compounds.
    Usage: <min order> <max order> [-alloy|-crystal] <number> <elements...>
    min order: Minimum number of constituents
    max order: Maximum number of constituents
    -alloy: Generate evenly-spaced compositions
    -crystal: Generate fractional compositions with small denominators (i.e. AB2, or A2B5)
    number: Either desired maximum spacing [-alloy], or maximum number of of atoms in the formula unit [-crystal]
    elements: List of elements to include in phase diagrams

      • generateAlloyCompositions

        protected java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.List<double[]>> generateAlloyCompositions()
        Generate evenly-spaced compositions. Generates compositions for all diagrams up to the user-specified MinOrder.

        For example: If the user wants ternary diagrams with a minimum spacing of 0.25, this code will generate the following map:
        1 -> ([1.0])
        2 -> ([0.25, 0.75], [0.5, 0.5], [0.75, 0.25])
        3 -> ([0.5, 0.25, 0.25], [0.25, 0.5, 0.25], [0.25, 0.25, 0.5])

        Returns:
        Map of number of elements -> Possible compositions

      • generateCrystalCompositions

        protected java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.List<double[]>> generateCrystalCompositions()
        Generate compositions with small denominators. Generates compositions for all diagrams up to the user-specified MinOrder.

        For example: If the user wants ternary diagrams with a maximum denominator of 3, this code will generate the following map:
        1 -> ([1])
        2 -> ([1/3, 2/3], [1/2, 1/2], [2/3, 1/3])
        3 -> ([1/3, 1/3, 1/3])

        Returns:
        Map of number of elements -> Possible compositions
